FBIS3-37105 "drsov030_m_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Tajikistan Border Guards Repel Attack LD1202161594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1527 GMT 12 Feb 94 LD1202161594 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] [Text] Moscow February 12 TASS -- The 3rd border post of the Pyanj border unit was attacked by a group of militants on February 11. The border detail and reinforcement defeated the enemy. A border guard was wounded, sources at the Russian border troops' press service told ITAR-TASS here today. Another fight was reported upon the reinforcement's return to the border post. The attackers were put under fire and defeated. The border section is now under full control. The 12th border post of the Moscow border unit was repeatedly shelled from the rear on the same day. The militants used fire arms, rockets and grenade launchers. All fire nests of the attackers were suppressed. The losses of militants are being specified. There are no casualties amongst border guards.
